{{Infobox person | name = Maria Renée Cura | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = Argentina | death_date = 12 July 2007 | death_place = | restingplace = | restingplacecoordinates = | othername = | occupation = Geographer, writer | yearsactive = | known for = | spouse = | domesticpartner = | children = | parents = | website = | awards = [[Padma Shri]] }} '''Maria Renée Cura''' was an Argentinian geographer, writer and [[Indologist]].<ref name="Environment and Human Response: Selected Essays in Geography">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.ae/books?id=30XFyeeYs5cC&pg=PR18&lpg=PR18&dq=Maria+Renee+Cura&source=bl&ots=B5vYV-Oq4p&sig=E18uwIvY4igl83Le1VXIjyPU4kA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CBsQ6AEwADgKahUKEwjbouG1zd_GAhVGcRQKHSCsDXk#v=onepage&q=Maria%20Renee%20Cura&f=false | title=Environment and Human Response: Selected Essays in Geography | publisher=Concept Publications | author=Ram Nandan Prasad Sinha | year=1990 | pages=340 | isbn=9788170222439}}</ref> She was the founder of ''Anand Bhavan'', a centre for Indological studies, at her native place, [[Chivilcoy]] in [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina, named after the present day [[Allahabad]] museum and the [[Anand Bhavan|former residence of Nehru family]].<ref name="Homage to Maria Rene Cura, 1 December 2007">{{cite web | url=http://latinamericanaffairs.blogspot.ae/2007/12/homage-to-maria-rene-cura-1-december.html | title=Homage to Maria Rene Cura, 1 December 2007 | publisher=Latin America Affairs | date=2 December 2007 | accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref>
==Works== Cura authored several books, ''Islas Malvinas y Antártida Argentina'',<ref name="Islas Malvinas y Antártida Argentina">{{cite web | url=http://www.werelate.org/wiki/Source:Cura,_Maria_Renee._Islas_Malvinas_y_Ant%C3%A1rtida_Argentina | title=Islas Malvinas y Antártida Argentina | publisher=We Relate | date=2015 | accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref> ''Islas Malvinas y Antártida Argentina'' and ''Islas Malvinas, Georgias, Sandwich del Sur y Antártida Argentina'' being some of the notable ones.<ref name="CURA, MARIA RENEE">{{cite web|url=http://www.bnm.me.gov.ar/cgi-bin/wxis.exe/opac/?IsisScript=opac/opac.xis&dbn=BINAM&tb=aut&src=link&query=CURA,%20MARIA%20RENEE&cantidad=10&formato=&sala=|title=Cura, Maria Renee|last=|first=|date=2015|website=|publisher=BNM|accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref> She also translated the ''Letters to the Young People'', a work by [[Indira Gandhi]],<ref name="Letters to the Young People">{{cite book | url=http://buenosaires.locanto.com.ar/ID_229991304/CARTAS-A-LA-GENTE-JOVEN-Traduccion-de-Maria-Renee-Cura.html | title=Letters to the Young People | publisher=Nivicke | author=Indira Gandhi (translation: Renée Maria Cura) | year=1982 | pages=127}}</ref> and started a magazine, ''India eterna y actual'', in 1987 which became defunct after her death.<ref name="Homage to Maria Rene Cura, 1 December 2007" /> She was the president of the ''South Foundation'', founded by [[Victoria Ocampo]]<ref name="The red suitcase of Victoria Ocampo">{{cite web | url=http://www.lanacion.com.ar/871341-la-valija-colorada-de-victoria-ocampo | title=The red suitcase of Victoria Ocampo | publisher=Lanacion | date=31 December 2006 | accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref> and maintained close associations with the Argentinian intellectual and [[Indira Gandhi]], the former prime minister of India.<ref name="This America of Ours: The Letters of Gabriela Mistral and Victoria Ocampo">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.ae/books?id=0XL-5rdOU-kC&pg=PR8&lpg=PR8&dq=Maria+Renee+Cura&source=bl&ots=mnWWjZFNum&sig=JYU6j7s4pBobnP0ASZG1TUxmdjw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CB4Q6AEwATgKahUKEwjbouG1zd_GAhVGcRQKHSCsDXk#v=onepage&q=Maria%20Renee%20Cura&f=false | title=This America of Ours: The Letters of Gabriela Mistral and Victoria Ocampo | publisher=University of Texas Press | author=Gabriela Mistral, Victoria Ocampo | year=2009 | isbn=9780292778603}}</ref> The [[Government of India]] awarded her the fourth highest Indian civilian honour of [[Padma Shri]] in 1984.<ref name="Padma Awards">{{cite web|url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |title=Padma Awards |publisher=Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India |date=2015 |accessdate=June 18, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6U68ulwpb?url=http://mha.nic.in/sites/upload_files/mha/files/LST-PDAWD-2013.pdf |archivedate=November 15, 2014 |df= }}</ref> Cura died on 12 July 2007.<ref name="Renée Maria Cura - Consultation and obituaries dead people">{{cite web | url=https://www.dateas.com/es/obituario/cura-maria-renee-289443 | title=Renée Maria Cura - Consultation and obituaries dead people | publisher=Date as | date=13 July 2007 | accessdate=July 17, 2015}}</ref>
